<br>
For example Rom's sig is 180 high, which means the space it takes on screen is over 10% of the vertical resolution. So if we have 10 posts with that tall sig, we have 1800 pixels of sigs in that thread and that's over one screenful... and nothing contributed to the thread. Whereas if they were 60 high, you can fit 30 sigs in that same space... or if the same 10 posts took 1800 with 60 high sigs, it would mean there is like 800pixels worth of text to read. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
It's all about efficiency. *grin*<br>
<br>
But no, 200 isn't the worst case... the worst is the people with 200 high who put them 10x per thread and mods don't do anything. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
